I’ve been hiding this collaboration with @shop.solkyst for quite some time but the day is FINALLY here! 

I met @meghanvictoriax in the early days of starting content creation and I remember the exact reason we connected: everything otherworldly and spirituality. It’s not something I share very openly but the minute I met Meg I knew she would understand my way of being. 

This entire collection was born out of the belief that true beauty lies not in conforming to societal expectations, but in cherishing the raw and authentic elements that make us who we are. These sunglasses were designed to be more than just an accessory; they are a reminder that embracing our natural selves is a statement of strength and a testament to our individuality.  The name Jean is near and dear to my heart as it is dedicated to my late grandmother who passed away unexpectedly a few weeks ago. 

Whether you’re striding down the streets or strolling along the beach, may these shades serve as a constant reminder of your inherent fierceness. I am humbled by the opportunity to work alongside such a remarkable entrepreneur, women, and friend.
JEAN is officially available at @shop.solkyst with code BLONDEMANN to save some $$$

If you like the feeling of a minty fresh moment and dewy, hydrated skin this Cryo-Flash Cream-Mask from @clarinscanada is 5 ⭐️‘s (and that’s no joke go look at the ratings.) It feels like you’re icing your skin but that feeling lingers, very refreshing, very soothing and I’ve been struggling with my skin lately so I’ve been extra careful with what’s in my rotation. Great before an event for a pick me up too, noticed it really does help with the look of my pores, and the dew is dewwwwwwin’ it’s thing — get it?? Tested for just under a month before I committed to this #ad. Worth the hype! #clarinscanada #cryoflashcreammask
